Abstraction
  displaying the essential information, an hiding the rest.
Attributes / Properties
  allows you to specify additional information to the compiler to enforce constraints
Class
  It is a user-defined data type
Class Variable
  name given to a memory location
Composition 
  building complex objects from simpler ones
Encapsulation
  combining data members and functions in a single unit
Friends
  A non-member function can access the private and protected members of a class if it is declared a friend of that class
Inheritance
  creating new classes which retain characteristics of the base class. 
Instance Variable
  a variable defined in a class for which each instantiated object of the class has a separate copy
Member Variable
   variable that is associated with a specific object
Method
   procedure or function in OOPs Concepts
Multiple Inheritance
  a class can inherit from more than one classes. 
Object
  instances of class, which holds the data variables declared in class and the member functions work on these class objects
Overloading
  Function overloading is a feature in C++ where two or more functions can have the same name but different parameters
Polymorphism
  all to a member function will cause a different function to be executed depending on the type of object that invokes the function
Public / Private / Protected
  is part of a class, public any function can accese the information. private only funtions apart of the class can acceese it. protected any can accese it but not change it.
